title: Production of fragments of mass number 6<=A<=11 in 12C, 14N and 16O spallation by alpha-particles at energies near threshold.

x4freetext: Production of fragments of mass number 6<=A<=11 in 12C,
14N and 16O spallation by alpha-particles at energies

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuovo Cimento A, Vol.49, p.235 (1979)

x4freetext: Alpha-particle beam. Cross sections represent an
average over the energy interval of 25-60 MeV and
centered at mean incident energy E=33.4 MeV. The mean
energy of incident alpha particles is found to be
three energy regions of about 10 MeV width.
Incident angle was 45 degrees and approximate flux
